# Documentation Standards

- Use forward slashes in docs, rules, skills, and Markdown links.
- Keep setup and usage instructions practical and testable.
- When creating installation or operating docs, include Windows, macOS, and Linux instructions.
- Prefer concise path, purpose, and command examples over long prose.
- Do not duplicate large source material; link to source files and summarize the role.
- Update `PROJECT_INDEX.md` when docs change how agents should navigate the repo.
